content.description: One move wonder!! Start on two crimps and pop to sloper over the lip. The Gentlemen was hitting the hold.
content.location: left end of boulder with Can We Cane 'Em.

content.description: Start sitting on the right side of the face on the can we cane'em Boulder.  Traverse the lip all the way to the left arÃªte.  More or less an extension to Can We Cane 'em.  Full value and quite safe.
content.location: Just in the trees above the talus above Pete's Pebble.

content.description:
Start under roof with hands squeezing each side.  Slap out left and then move right up corner.  This is actually really fun and a good little warm up.   

  I broke off the top finishing jug and took a nasty fall, hence the name.  Good and clean now.
content.location: This boulder is up hill and left approx 50ft of Can we cane em.

content.description: Start on left of two crimps with right hand and left hand on slope side pull. Climb out left of roof and top out.
content.protection: pads lots of them to fill in the holes
content.location: This is the left version of the Power Plant Boulder. Starts left of Power Plant line.

content.description: Start on lower two holds move up to side pulls on lip to move left to top out. Super good traverse.
content.location: walk to far right side of 500 foot boulder field. Head up talus to woods on right. Boulders are near top of the woods. Super slap in straight up from these woods.

content.description: Starts low under roof and move up to to large feature and move right to lip and top out. There are hold all the way to the lip.
content.location: walk to far right side of 500 foot boulder field. Head up talus to woods on right. Boulders are near top of the woods. Super slap in straight up from these woods. Right of can we cane em about fifty feet.

content.description: A bench of a boulder, long and low.  In the woods.
